author: The Current
description:
Alabama-born singer-songwriter Kashus Culpepper delivers a solo acoustic performance of his song, “Better Weather,” standing alongside the railway tracks near Utepils Brewing in Minneapolis. Although this was filmed in Minnesota, the train tracks provide a picturesque spot for an artist who is such a reverent purveyor of Southern music — country, soul, blues, folk, and rock.

Musician 
Kashus Culpepper – vocals, guitar

author: The Current
description: Dizzy Fae’s futuristic dance track “Right Side” is a spirit booster. The Minnesota-bred pop/R&B artist leans on her limitless ability to play and experiment with sound. “Right Side” can be heard station-wide on The Current. Be on the lookout for even more new tracks from Dizzy Fae, including Sunday nights on The Local Show. Hit Play!
title: Hit Play: @DizzyFae talks about her futuristic dance track “Right Side.” #dizzyfae #shorts #music
